│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                               │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The transformation produces a wrong exit value for a uniform induction with   │
│ an outside use. Source returns 8, but the target returns 7. In the vectorized │
│ IR, the middle.block selects %3 from vector.body, where %3 = add i32 %step.2, │
│ %0 and %0 is the current index. At the last vector iteration with VF=2,       │
│ index=6, so %3=7, while the correct exit is 8. The exit value must correspond │
│ to the last processed lane's post-increment, i.e., index.next or an extract   │
│ of the last lane, not the current index + step.                               │
│                                                                               │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                       │
│ ScalarEvolution confirms the loop trip is 8 and iv.next ranges up to 9 with   │
│ final exit value 8. The produced vector plan wires the exit value from the    │
│ middle block to %3 (step + index), which corresponds to the first lane's next │
│ value, not the last lane's. The first transformation identified is            │
│ VPlanTransforms::removeDeadRecipes, but the symptom stems from the plan       │
│ wiring of exit users for inductions: addUsersInExitBlocks deliberately skips  │
│ handling induction exit values, relying on separate logic. Consequently, the  │
│ VPIRInstruction in the exit ends up using the wrong value from the vector     │
│ body (%3) without applying the “last lane” fix.                               │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ In LoopVectorize.cpp:addUsersInExitBlocks, exit users are scanned and         │
│ VPIRInstructions updated. Induction exit values are currently handled outside │
│ VPlan and addUsersInExitBlocks skips them if isOptimizableIVOrUse(V) and      │
│ predecessor is middle.block. For our uniform IV with outside use, this skip   │
│ prevents adding the necessary extract/select to use the last lane's value. As │
│ a result, the exit phi takes the operand from the vector body (%3 = step +    │
│ index), which is the first lane, yielding 7 instead of 8. The intended        │
│ behavior (per comments around 8886 and elsewhere) is that induction           │
│ resume/exit values should use the last lane (or index.next for VF=2).         │
│ Therefore, either the separate induction-exit handling did not run before     │
│ this wiring, or it is insufficient for this case; in any case,                │
│ addUsersInExitBlocks must not skip fixing operands for induction exit users   │
│ when the only available value is lane-ambiguous.                              │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ Edit file llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp, lines 9070-9104    │
│ (function addUsersInExitBlocks): remove the special-case skip for induction   │
│ exit users (isOptimizableIVOrUse) so that exit users receive an               │
│ ExtractFromEnd of the last lane by default. This ensures that for inductions  │
│ with outside uses, the middle.block feeds the correct value (last lane) to    │
│ the exit phi.                                                                 │
│                                                                               │
