│   if (isOptimizableIVOrUse(V) && ExitVPBB->getSinglePredecessor() ==          │
│ MiddleVPBB)                                                                   │
│     continue;                                                                 │
│ with code that marks these for fixing or directly applies the                 │
│ extract-from-end, i.e., delete the conditional continue and let the existing  │
│ loop create ExtractFromEnd for non-live-ins. The current logic already        │
│ creates ExtractFromEnd for operands coming from the middle block; removing    │
│ the skip enforces the last-lane semantics.                                    │
│                                                                               │
│ This change ensures VPIRInstructions modeling LCSSA phis in the exit block    │
│ get their operand adjusted to the last lane, matching the expected exit value │
│ (8).                                                                          │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ By removing the skip in addUsersInExitBlocks for induction-related exit       │
│ users, we guarantee that the exit block uses the last-lane value (or          │
│ index.next), fixing the off-by-one and aligning the vectorized IR with the    │
│ scalar semantics. This corrects %res to be 8 instead of 7 for the reproducer, │
│ without relying on fragile external induction-exit handling paths.            │
